ers and pilots in these two incidents contrasts markedly with previous incidents in which Soviet fighters attacked Western planes. Soviet attacks on Western aircraft usually have occurred when Soviet radar has indicated that the intruder had violated Soviet-claimed territorial limits.\n\nThe failure by Soviet air defense authorities to order attacks in recent cases raises the possibility that for policy reasons Moscow has ordered Soviet air defense authorities to exercise restraint at this time in reacting to overflights of Soviet boundaries", "token_count": 88, "token_end_0based": 87, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "comment the restrained attitude displayed by soviet ground controllers and pilots in these two incidents contrasts markedly with previous incidents in which soviet fighters attacked western planes soviet attacks on western aircraft usually have occurred when soviet radar has indicated that the intruder had violated soviet-claimed territorial limits the failure by soviet air defense authorities to order attacks in recent cases raises the possibility that for policy reasons moscow has ordered soviet air defense authorities to exercise restraint at this time in reacting to overflights of soviet boundaries", "unred_source_page": 4}
